data.enText: to attract sb or make sb want to do or have sth, even if they know it is wrong

data.chText: 甜食菜单馋得我垂涎欲滴。
data.enText: I was tempted by the dessert menu.

data.chText: 别把贵重物品放在显眼处招贼。
data.enText: Don't tempt thieves by leaving valuables clearly visible.

data.chText: 我动了心，想那一天休假。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: I was tempted to take the day off.
to persuade or try to persuade sb to do sth that you want them to do, for example by offering them sth

data.chText: 我们怎么才能吸引年轻人学习工程学呢？
data.enText: How can we tempt young people into engineering?

data.chText: 什么也吸引不了我到这里居住。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: Nothing would tempt me to live here.
to do sth too confidently in a way that might mean that your good luck will come to an end

ex.chText: 他企图引诱她离开丈夫和家庭。
ex.enText: He attempted to lure her away from her husband and family.

ex.chText: 电脑游戏诱惑着青少年，分散了他们学习的注意力。
ex.enText: Computer games are luring youngsters away from study.

synonyms.bx: 尤指诱使某人做错误或危险的事。

ex.enText: He was allured by her beauty.
He was allured from the country.

synonyms.bx: 通常指美好的事物使人受到吸引或诱惑。

ex.enText: The boy was enticed into playing truant.

ex.chText: 他们的特价优惠是为了吸引人们购买。
ex.enText: Their special offers are intended to entice people to buy.

ex.chText: 她诱惑他来参加她的生日派对。
ex.enText: She enticed him to come to her birthday party.

synonyms.bx: 通常指以诱人的东西说服某人做某事或去某处。

ex.chText: 他当时很年轻，抵挡不住巴黎的诱惑。
ex.enText: He was very young and seduced by Paris.

ex.chText: 其他地方更优厚的薪金待遇诱使他离开了公司。
ex.enText: He was seduced into leaving the company by the offer of higher pay elsewhere.

ex.chText: 他因诱奸女学生而被解雇。
ex.enText: He was fired for seducing female students.

synonyms.bx: 指诱使某人做通常不会做的事，常用被动语态；也指诱使某人发生性关系。

ex.chText: 他的朋友怂恿他去偷东西。
ex.enText: His friend tempted him to steal.

ex.chText: 没有人能骗他去干这样的傻事。
ex.enText: No one can tempt him to do such a foolish thing.

ex.chText: 我忍不住想买那顶帽子。
ex.enText: I'm tempted to buy that hat.

synonyms.bx: 指怂恿某人做某事，或引诱某人做明知不对的事，语义较弱。

data.enText: to do sth too confidently in a way that might mean that your good luck will come to an end

tr: induce into action by using one's charm
example: She charmed him into giving her all his money

tr: provoke someone to do something through (often false or exaggerated) promises or persuasion

example: St. Anthony was tempted in the desert

tr: dispose or incline or entice to
example: We were tempted by the delicious-looking food

tr: give rise to a desire by being attractive or inviting
example: the window displays tempted the shoppers

value.def: Something that tempts you attracts you and makes you want it, even though it may be wrong or harmful.

example.ex: Reducing the income will further impoverish these families and could tempt an offender into further crime...
example.tran: 降低收入只会使这些家庭更加贫穷，而且可能诱使不法分子进一步犯罪。

example.ex: It is the fresh fruit that tempts me at this time of year...
example.tran: 一年当中这个时节，新鲜水果最能吸引我了。

example.ex: Can I tempt you with a little puff pastry?...
example.tran: 我能给你尝点泡芙点心吗？

example.ex: The fact that she had become wealthy did not tempt her to alter her frugal way of life.
example.tran: 她有钱了，可这丝毫没能让她改变节俭的生活习惯。

value.def: If you tempt someone, you offer them something they want in order to encourage them to do what you want them to do.

example.ex: ...a million dollar marketing campaign to tempt American tourists back to Britain...
example.tran: 耗资百万美元试图把美国游客重新吸引到英国来的营销活动

example.ex: Having spent so long at a great club like Rangers, no other Scottish team could tempt him away...
example.tran: 在流浪者队这样优秀的俱乐部呆了这么久之后，其他苏格兰球队都吸引不了他了。

example.ex: Don't let credit tempt you to buy something you can't afford...
example.tran: 不要因为可以赊购，就买超过自己支付能力的东西。

example.ex: She will be offering a package worth about 40 million dollars, to tempt the rebels into agreeing to disarm.
example.tran: 她将提出价值 4, 000 万美元的一揽子条件，以诱使反叛分子答应解除武装。

value.def: If someone says that something they say or do is tempting fate or is tempting providence, they mean they are worried that it may cause the good luck they have had so far to end.

example.ex: As soon as you start to talk about never having played on a losing side, it is tempting fate.
example.tran: 你刚说从来没输过，晦气就来了。

value.tran: 说晦气话，玩过火，冒险（使好运结束）

partsOfSpeech.dec: at 加强 + tempt 尝试 → 尝试，企图
tempt 尝试 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 想尝试一下 → 诱惑
tempt 尝试 + atious 有…性质的 → 诱惑性的
tempt 尝试 + ing 令人…的 → 吸引人的；动人的
con 加强 + tempt 蔑视 → 轻视
contempt 轻视 + ible 可…的 → 可轻视的；下贱的
contempt 轻视 + uous …的 → 瞧不起人的
